{{Otheruses|Beta}}
{{Quote|During your travels, you must try to find out, discreetly, what the Empire wants with, say, the Beta System. Are there valuable resources in the system? Is it a strategic port? Does some important personage visit there on holiday? Does the Grand Moff of the sector particularly enjoy one of the local wines?|Airen Cracken|<ref name="GK">''[[Star Wars Gamemaster Kit]]''</ref>}}
'''Beta system''' was a generic code used by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] to designate [[Star system/Legends|star systems]] with a [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] presence. [[General/Legends|General]] [[Airen Cracken/Legends|Airen Cracken]] used the system as an example while briefing new Rebel agents.<ref name="GK" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[Jason Fry]], co-author of ''[[The Essential Atlas]]'', indicated in [[June]] [[2015]] that the Beta system was excluded from [[Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion|''The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion]] because it was an imaginary location used as an example.<ref name="Email">{{EmailCite|email=File:EAOC discussion.jpg|creator=Jason Fry|date=2015-06-30}}</ref>

